    <p>
      These are the requirements for all homework assignments.
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            On all problems, you must show all work necessary to justify your solution.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            On all problems, you must find a way to explain your reasoning.  You must do this in complete sentences.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            In your explanations and supporting work, do your best to demonstrate your understanding of the problem and the concepts used to solve them.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Make sure you carefully check the accuracy of your computations.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      You may turn in your assignment as a hard copy in class, or you may submit your assignment electronically on Blackboard.  <alert>If you turn in your assignment electronically, you <em>must</em> convert it to a PDF file</alert>.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <p>
    Here are the problems for this assignment.  You can find them at the end of Section  of our textbook.  You may use the PDF version of the book, which can be found on Blackboard under <q>Course Information &amp; Resources</q>, or you may use the online version by clicking on on <url href="">this link</url> and scrolling down to the bottom of the page.
